{"title_page": "2018 Campeones Cup", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox football match\n| title              = 2018 Campeones Cup\n| image              = BMO Field in 2016.png\n| imagesize          = 250\n| caption            = [[BMO Field]] in [[Toronto]] hosted the match\n| event              = [[Campeones Cup]]\n| team1              = [[Toronto FC]]\n| team1association   = {{flagicon|CAN|size=30px}}\n| team1score         = 1\n| team2              = [[Tigres UANL|UANL]]\n| team2association   = {{flagicon|MEX|size=30px}}\n| team2score         = 3\n| details            =\n| date               = {{Start date|2018|9|19|df=y}}\n| stadium            = [[BMO Field]]\n| city               = [[Toronto]]\n| man_of_the_match1a = [[Jes\u00fas Due\u00f1as]] (UANL)<ref name=\"MOTM\">{{cite news |last=Boehm |first=Charles |url=https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2018-09-19-toronto-fc-vs-tigres-uanl/recap |title=Toronto FC 1, Tigres UANL 3 \u2013 2018 Campeones Cup Match Recap |website=MLSsoccer.com |publisher=[[Major League Soccer]] |date=19 September 2018 |access-date=19 September 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920031330/https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2018-09-19-toronto-fc-vs-tigres-uanl/recap |archive-date=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n| referee            = [[Ricardo Montero (referee)|Ricardo Montero]] {{nowrap|([[Costa Rican Football Federation|Costa Rica]])}}<ref name=\"rules\"/>\n| attendance         = 14,823<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/09/20/nc-america/campeones-cup/toronto-fc/club-tigres-de-la-unl/2843850/ |title=Toronto vs. Tigres UANL \u2013 20 September 2018 |website=Soccerway |publisher=[[Perform Group]] |date=19 September 2018 |access-date=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n| weather            = Clear<br>{{convert|18|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|abbr=on}}<br>73% [[humidity]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wunderground.com/history/daily/ca/toronto/CYYZ/date/2018-9-19 |title=Toronto-Pearson International, Canada History |website=[[Weather Underground (weather service)|Weather Underground]] |publisher=[[The Weather Company]] |date=19 September 2018 |access-date=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n| next               = [[2019 Campeones Cup|2019]]\n}}\nThe '''2018 Campeones Cup''' was the first edition of the [[Campeones Cup]], an annual North American [[Association football|football]] competition contested between the champions of the previous [[Major League Soccer]] season and the winner of the [[Campe\u00f3n de Campeones]] from [[Liga MX]].\n\nThe match featured Canadian side [[Toronto FC]], winners of the [[MLS Cup 2017]], and [[Tigres UANL|UANL]], winners of the [[2018 Campe\u00f3n de Campeones]], for which they qualified by winning the [[2017\u201318 Liga MX season#Torneo Apertura|2017 Liga MX Torneo Apertura]]. Toronto FC hosted the match at [[BMO Field]] in [[Toronto]], Canada on 19 September 2018.\n\nUANL won the match 3\u20131 to win the inaugural Campeones Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/article-mexicos-tigres-get-a-little-payback-defeat-toronto-fc-in-campeones/|title=Mexico\u2019s Tigres get a little payback, defeat Toronto FC in Campeones Cup|publisher=theglobeandmail.com|date=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Teams==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Team\n!Qualification\n|-\n|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[Toronto FC]]\n|[[MLS Cup 2017]] winners\n|-\n|{{flagicon|MEX}} [[Tigres UANL|UANL]]\n|[[2018 Campe\u00f3n de Campeones]] winners\n|}\n\n==Venue==\nAs the MLS team, Toronto FC hosted the match, which took place at [[BMO Field]] in [[Toronto]], with a seating capacity of 30,000, hosted the match. The stadium opened in 2007 and was renovated in 2016.<ref>{{cite news |date=5 May 2016 |title='A whole new stadium': Take a look at renovated BMO Field ahead of Toronto FC home opener |url=https://nationalpost.com/sports/soccer/a-whole-new-stadium-take-a-look-at-renovated-bmo-field-ahead-of-toronto-fc-home-opener |work=[[The National Post]] |access-date=11 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcasting==\n\nThe match's English broadcast was aired in Canada on [[The Sports Network|TSN]] and the United States on [[ESPN2]]. A French broadcast was aired in Canada on [[TVA Sports 2]], while [[Univision]] and [[Univision Deportes Network]] carried the Spanish broadcast in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |date=September 17, 2018 |title=Univision, ESPN, TSN and TVA Sports sign long-term Campeones Cup deal |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2018/09/17/univision-espn-tsn-and-tva-sports-sign-long-term-campeones-cup-deal |publisher=MLSsoccer.com |accessdate=December 7, 2018}}</ref> The Univision broadcast was watched by an audience of 1.1 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Werner |first=Collin |date=September 29, 2018 |title=Most-watched soccer games on US TV for September 18-23, 2018 |url=http://worldsoccertalk.com/2018/09/29/watched-soccer-games-us-tv-september-18-23-2018/ |work=World Soccer Talk |accessdate=December 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Match==\n\n===Details===\n<onlyinclude>{{Football box\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|9|19|df=y}}\n|time       = 20:15 [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n|team1      = [[Toronto FC]] {{flagicon|CAN}}\n|score      = 1\u20133\n|report     = https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2018-09-19-toronto-fc-vs-tigres-uanl/boxscore\n|team2      = {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Tigres UANL|UANL]]\n|goals1     =\n*[[Lucas Janson|Janson]] {{goal|87|pen.}}\n|goals2     =\n*[[Jes\u00fas Due\u00f1as|Due\u00f1as]] {{goal|36||64}}\n*[[Eriq Zavaleta|Zavaleta]] {{goal|66|o.g.}}\n|stadium    = [[BMO Field]], [[Toronto]]\n|attendance = 14,823\n|referee    = [[Ricardo Montero (referee)|Ricardo Montero]] ([[Costa Rican Football Federation|Costa Rica]])\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n{| width=92%\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n |pattern_la = _torontofc17h\n |pattern_b  = _torontofc17H\n |pattern_ra = _torontofc17h\n |pattern_sh = _torontofc17h\n |pattern_so = _torontofc17h\n |leftarm    = 223241\n |body       = EB0000\n |right