Press, 2007. {{ISBN|978-0-19-530665-1}}.\n* Clouse, Jerry Allan. ''The Whiskey Rebellion: Southwestern Pennsylvania's Frontier People Test the American Constitution'' (Bureau of Historic Preservation, Pennsylvania Historical and Museum Commission, 1994)  \n* Krom, Cynthia L., and Stephanie Krom. \"The Whiskey Tax of 1791 and The Consequent Insurrection: 'A Wicked and Happy Tumult'.\" ''Accounting Historians Journal'' 40.2 (2013): 91-113. [https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Cynthia_Krom/publication/299482960_The_Whiskey_Tax_of_1791_and_the_consequent_insurrection_A_wicked_and_unhappy_tumult/links/56faa4f008ae1b40b804d2ef/The-Whiskey-Tax-of-1791-and-the-consequent-insurrection-A-wicked-and-unhappy-tumult online]\n* McClure, James P. \"'Let Us Be Independent': David Bradford and the Whiskey Insurrection.\" ''Western Pennsylvania History'' 74.2 (1991): 72-86. [https://journals.psu.edu/wph/article/viewFile/4262/4079 online]\n* Snyder, Jeffrey W., and Thomas C. Hammond. \"'So That's What the Whiskey Rebellion Was!': Teaching Early US History With GIS.\" ''History Teacher'' 45.3 (2012): 447-455. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/23265898 online]\n* Yoo, John. \"George Washington and the Executive Power.\" ''University of St. Thomas Journal of Law and Public Policy'' 5 (2010): 1-35. [https://scholarship.law.berkeley.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2272&context=facpubs online]\n\n===Sources from 1790s===\n* [[Henry Marie Brackenridge|Brackenridge, Henry Marie]]. [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_PycYAAAAYAAJ <!-- quote=brackenridge whiskey. --> ''History of the Western Insurrection in Western Pennsylvania&nbsp;...''] Pittsburgh, 1859.\n* [[Hugh Henry Brackenridge|Brackenridge, Hugh Henry]]. ''Incidents of the Insurrection in Western Pennsylvania in the Year 1794''. Philadelphia, 1795. A 1972 edition has notes by Daniel Marder.\n* [[William Findley|Findley, William]]. [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_RXsFAAAAQAAJ <!-- quote=William Findley, History of the Insurrection. -->